laboratory_examinations.findings: Mild dependent atelectasis bilaterally in the lower chest. The liver, pancreas, spleen, and adrenal glands are normal. Kidneys are normal in size and symmetric with no lesions or hydronephrosis. The stomach, small bowel, colon, and rectum are normal. The appendix measures up to 8 mm with no surrounding fat stranding. There is a 3.6 x 2.6 x 3.5 cm hyperdense right uterine structure with blood vessels, but no lymphadenopathy. No free fluid in the pelvis.
